data.title: etnies PAS House for Public Domaine La Gaite Lyrique
data.tags: etnies,skateboarding,Pierre-Andre Senizergues,25th anniversary,Next 25,Public Domaine,La Gaite,Paris,Jose Rojo,Kyle Leeper
data.description: Imagine a city of the future where skateboards are used as the primary form of transportation and recreation – in and out of your home. A utopia city for skateboarders would mean that a skateable path, like a ribbon connecting everything together, links each building in an unending ability to keep in motion on your board. The PAS House takes this concept and brings it to life through an architectural project mixing a modern single family home with a skateboard ramp structure – all from an environmentally-driven perspective.

data.title: Emerica Presents: The Hsu G6
data.description:
Emerica is proud to announce the release of Jerry Hsu’s new pro model shoe, the Hsu G6; a remastered classic with a redesigned lightweight build: http://emerica.com/shoes/the-hsu-g6/black-white/

“I wanted a clean light weight shoe that protected me. I really love my first shoe, so to evolve from there was the only way I wanted to go.” - Jerry

And that’s what Jerry got.

This is the lightest Vulc Mid on the market and with the newly developed Internal Cage, the Hsu G6 won’t bag out. Available now at #HigherQuality skate shops everywhere.
